    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi dei eterni. <persName ref="#people/110"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Hludouicus</persName> vir divina clemencia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Habens pre occulis iudicii
                        examem divini cognitum fieri volumus, eo quod <persName ref="#people/55"
                            key="#Emperor/king">Angilberga</persName> dilectissima coniux nostra et
                            <rs key="#Queen">consors inperrii</rs> nostre humiliter suggessit
                        maiestati sese per divinum auxilium in lactere <placeName ref="#places/43"
                            key="#Cities #Roads #Public_infrastructures #Monasteries"
                            >Placentine</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">urbis</rs> in dei nomine velle <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs> construere. Qua de causa donamus et tradimus ei <rs
                            key="#Canals">canalle</rs> unum aque vive fluentis a <placeName
                            ref="#places/1980">Treuia</placeName> iusta <rs key="#Churches"
                            >bassilicam</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/94">sancte Brigide</orgName> et per <rs
                            key="#Forests">viridarium</rs> eiusdem cenobii usque in fossam Augustam,
                        ac stabilimus ubicumque voluerit infra ipsam urbem Placentinam <rs
                            key="#Roads #Public_infrastructures">stratas plubicas</rs> ad sui
                        monasterii dilandandas fines. Si quis autem haec nostra statuta infringere
                        quaesierit, dei omnipotentis iram incurrat et insuper poenam, quod est
                        multam <rs key="#Penalty">duodecim auri obrizi lib.</rs> componat,
                        medietatem camere nostre et sepe dicende coniugi nostre, cui iniuriam
                        inferre non timuit. Et haec nostre donacionis maiorem roborem optineat,
                        manus nostre propria ex bulla iusimus adnoctari.   Signum manus (M.) donni
                        Hludouicii serenissimi inperatoris.   Dat. II idus octub., indictione VIIII,
                        anno inperri donni Hludouici XXXV; ad <geogName ref="#estates/139"
                            key="#Curtes"><placeName ref="#places/342" key="#Curtes"
                                >Conlona</placeName>
                            <rs key="#Curtes">corte</rs></geogName> inperri; feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
